Algorithm description: 

The new algorithm calculates the scores for the bins by taking the product of the absolute differences between each value and the item size, summing up all the products, and dividing the scores by the minimum capacity multiplied by the cube root of the item size.

Code:
code:
import numpy as np

def score(item, bins):
    abs_diff = np.abs(bins - item)
    product_diff = np.prod(abs_diff)
    scores = product_diff / (np.min(bins) * np.cbrt(item))
    
    return scores
